  "title": "CNC Supervisor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>The CNC Supervisor is responsible for overseeing daily CNC machining operations to ensure production</p><p>targets, quality standards, and safety requirements are met. This role leads a team of machinists, supports</p><p>continuous improvement, and ensures compliance with engineering drawings, process controls, and</p><p>company procedures.<br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities  (Night Shift)</strong></p><p>• Supervise and coordinate daily CNC machining operations (Turning, Milling, Multi-axis,</p><p>etc.)</p><p>• Lead, train, and motivate CNC machinists and operators</p><p>• Ensure production schedules, output targets, and delivery timelines are achieved</p><p>• Monitor machine performance, tooling usage, and process efficiency</p><p>• Troubleshoot machining, tooling, and quality issues on the shop floor</p><p>• Ensure strict adherence to engineering drawings, work instructions, and specifications</p><p>• Implement and maintain quality standards (ISO 9001)</p><p>• Work closely with Production, Engineering, Quality, and Maintenance teams</p><p>• Enforce workplace safety, 5S, and housekeeping standards</p><p>• Assist in continuous improvement initiatives (Lean, Kaizen, cost reduction)</p><p>• Prepare reports on production performance, manpower, and machine utilisation.<br /></p><p><strong>Requirements & Qualifications</strong></p><p>• Diploma or Higher Nitec in Mechanical Engineering, Precision Engineering, or related field</p><p>• Minimum 3–5 years of hands-on CNC machining experience, with supervisory experience preferred</p><p>• Strong knowledge of CNC Turning and/or Milling processes</p><p>• Ability to read and interpret engineering drawings and GD&T</p><p>• Experience with precision components and tight tolerances</p><p>• Familiar with measuring instruments (CMM, micrometers, gauges, etc.)</p><p>• Good leadership, communication, and problem-solving skills</p><p>• Knowledge of safety regulations and manufacturing best practices in Singapore<br /></p><p><strong>Benefit:</strong></p><p>. Annual Leave </p><p>. Medical Claim $300 per year</p><p>. AWS and Performance Bonus</p><p>. Stable and Established Company</p><p>. Working hours: Monday – Friday 8:30am – 6pm</p><p>. Work location: Woodlands</p>",
